# MyMoolah — Project Overview

**MyMoolah** is a banking-grade Treasury Platform for South Africa.
- **Services**: Digital wallet, double-entry ledger, VAS (airtime/data/electricity/bills), USDC/stablecoin, NFC deposits, KYC, automated multi-supplier reconciliation
- **Production**: api-mm.mymoolah.africa | wallet.mymoolah.africa
- **Stack**: Node.js + Express, PostgreSQL (Cloud SQL), React + Vite, GCP (Cloud Run, GCS, Secret Manager, Cloud SQL Auth Proxy)
- **Standards**: Mojaloop-compliant, ISO 20022, POPIA, banking-grade security
- **For current status and priorities**: always read `docs/agent_handover.md` first

## Environment Architecture

| Environment | DB | Users | API Credentials | Access |
|------------|-----|-------|----------------|--------|
| UAT | GCS Cloud SQL UAT | Test users | UAT/test credentials | Codespaces port 6543 |
| Staging | GCS Cloud SQL Staging | Test users | Live production credentials | Codespaces port 6544 |
| Production | GCS Cloud SQL Production | Real clients | Live production credentials | Codespaces port 6545 |

## Quick Reference — DO / DON'T

| ✅ DO | ❌ DON'T |
|------|----------|
| Read rules + handover before work | Start without rules confirmation |
| Sweep `scripts/` before creating new scripts | Create scripts without checking (200+ exist) |
| Use `scripts/db-connection-helper.js` for ALL DB queries | Write custom DB connection logic |
| Use `docs/DATABASE_CONNECTION_GUIDE.md` for DB work | Skip reading the DB guide |
| Test in Codespaces only | Test on local machine |
| Run migrations before seeding | Seed before migrations |
| Use `./scripts/run-migrations-master.sh [uat\|staging\|production]` | Run `npx sequelize-cli` directly |
| Create session log when work is done | Wait for session end to document |
| Commit AND push after changes | Leave push for user |
| Get approval before destructive actions | Make destructive changes without confirmation |
| Flag tech debt in `docs/CURSOR_2.0_RULES_FINAL.md` | Leave architectural issues undocumented |

